#: ../../../changelog.rst:3
msgid "Changelog"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:2
msgid "2.6.3 (2026-01-07)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:4
msgid ""
"Fixed a high-severity security issue where decompression-bomb safeguards of "
"the streaming API were bypassed when HTTP redirects were followed. "
"(`GHSA-38jv-5279-wg99 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/security/"
"advisories/GHSA-38jv-5279-wg99>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:7
msgid ""
"Started treating ``Retry-After`` times greater than 6 hours as 6 hours by "
"default. (`#3743 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3743>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:9
msgid ""
"Fixed ``urllib3.connection.VerifiedHTTPSConnection`` on Emscripten. (`#3752 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3752>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:14
msgid "2.6.2 (2025-12-11)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:16
msgid ""
"Fixed ``HTTPResponse.read_chunked()`` to properly handle leftover data in "
"the decoder's buffer when reading compressed chunked responses. (`#3734 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3734>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:22
msgid "2.6.1 (2025-12-08)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:24
msgid ""
"Restore previously removed ``HTTPResponse.getheaders()`` and ``HTTPResponse."
"getheader()`` methods. (`#3731 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3731>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:30
msgid "2.6.0 (2025-12-05)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:33
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:35
msgid ""
"Fixed a security issue where streaming API could improperly handle highly "
"compressed HTTP content (\"decompression bombs\") leading to excessive "
"resource consumption even when a small amount of data was requested. Reading "
"small chunks of compressed data is safer and much more efficient now. "
"(`GHSA-2xpw-w6gg-jr37 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/security/"
"advisories/GHSA-2xpw-w6gg-jr37>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:40
msgid ""
"Fixed a security issue where an attacker could compose an HTTP response with "
"virtually unlimited links in the ``Content-Encoding`` header, potentially "
"leading to a denial of service (DoS) attack by exhausting system resources "
"during decoding. The number of allowed chained encodings is now limited to "
"5. (`GHSA-gm62-xv2j-4w53 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/security/"
"advisories/GHSA-gm62-xv2j-4w53>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:47
msgid ""
"If urllib3 is not installed with the optional `urllib3[brotli]` extra, but "
"your environment contains a Brotli/brotlicffi/brotlipy package anyway, make "
"sure to upgrade it to at least Brotli 1.2.0 or brotlicffi 1.2.0.0 to benefit "
"from the security fixes and avoid warnings. Prefer using `urllib3[brotli]` "
"to install a compatible Brotli package automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:53
msgid ""
"If you use custom decompressors, please make sure to update them to respect "
"the changed API of ``urllib3.response.ContentDecoder``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:58 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:94
#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:117 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:141
#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:166
msgid "Features"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:60
msgid ""
"Enabled retrieval, deletion, and membership testing in ``HTTPHeaderDict`` "
"using bytes keys. (`#3653 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3653>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:61
msgid ""
"Added host and port information to string representations of "
"``HTTPConnection``. (`#3666 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3666>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:62
msgid ""
"Added support for Python 3.14 free-threading builds explicitly. (`#3696 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3696>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:66
msgid "Removals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:68
msgid ""
"Removed the ``HTTPResponse.getheaders()`` method in favor of ``HTTPResponse."
"headers``. Removed the ``HTTPResponse.getheader(name, default)`` method in "
"favor of ``HTTPResponse.headers.get(name, default)``. (`#3622 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3622>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:73 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:102
#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:125 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:151
#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:171
msgid "Bugfixes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:75
msgid ""
"Fixed redirect handling in ``urllib3.PoolManager`` when an integer is passed "
"for the retries parameter. (`#3649 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3649>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:77
msgid ""
"Fixed ``HTTPConnectionPool`` when used in Emscripten with no explicit port. "
"(`#3664 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3664>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:78
msgid ""
"Fixed handling of ``SSLKEYLOGFILE`` with expandable variables. (`#3700 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3700>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:82 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:131
msgid "Misc"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:84
msgid ""
"Changed the ``zstd`` extra to install ``backports.zstd`` instead of "
"``zstandard`` on Python 3.13 and before. (`#3693 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/3693>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:85
msgid ""
"Improved the performance of content decoding by optimizing "
"``BytesQueueBuffer`` class. (`#3710 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3710>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:86
msgid ""
"Allowed building the urllib3 package with newer setuptools-scm v9.x. (`#3652 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3652>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:87
msgid ""
"Ensured successful urllib3 builds by setting Hatchling requirement to >= "
"1.27.0. (`#3638 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3638>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:91
msgid "2.5.0 (2025-06-18)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:96
msgid ""
"Added support for the ``compression.zstd`` module that is new in Python "
"3.14. See `PEP 784 <https://peps.python.org/pep-0784/>`_ for more "
"information. (`#3610 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3610>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:98
msgid ""
"Added support for version 0.5 of ``hatch-vcs`` (`#3612 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/3612>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:104
msgid ""
"Fixed a security issue where restricting the maximum number of followed "
"redirects at the ``urllib3.PoolManager`` level via the ``retries`` parameter "
"did not work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:107
msgid ""
"Made the Node.js runtime respect redirect parameters such as ``retries`` and "
"``redirects``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:109
msgid ""
"Raised exception for ``HTTPResponse.shutdown`` on a connection already "
"released to the pool. (`#3581 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3581>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:110
msgid ""
"Fixed incorrect `CONNECT` statement when using an IPv6 proxy with "
"`connection_from_host`. Previously would not be wrapped in `[]`. (`#3615 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3615>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:114
msgid "2.4.0 (2025-04-10)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:119
msgid ""
"Applied PEP 639 by specifying the license fields in pyproject.toml. (`#3522 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3522>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:120
msgid ""
"Updated exceptions to save and restore more properties during the pickle/"
"serialization process. (`#3567 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3567>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:121
msgid ""
"Added ``verify_flags`` option to ``create_urllib3_context`` with a default "
"of ``VERIFY_X509_PARTIAL_CHAIN`` and ``VERIFY_X509_STRICT`` for Python "
"3.13+. (`#3571 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3571>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:127
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug with partial reads of streaming data in Emscripten. (`#3555 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3555>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:133
msgid ""
"Switched to uv for installing development dependecies. (`#3550 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3550>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:134
msgid ""
"Removed the ``multiple.intoto.jsonl`` asset from GitHub releases. "
"Attestation of release files since v2.3.0 can be found on PyPI. (`#3566 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3566>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:138
msgid "2.3.0 (2024-12-22)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:143
msgid ""
"Added ``HTTPResponse.shutdown()`` to stop any ongoing or future reads for a "
"specific response. It calls ``shutdown(SHUT_RD)`` on the underlying socket. "
"This feature was `sponsored by LaunchDarkly <https://opencollective.com/"
"urllib3/contributions/815307>`__. (`#2868 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2868>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:144
msgid ""
"Added support for JavaScript Promise Integration on Emscripten. This enables "
"more efficient WebAssembly requests and streaming, and makes it possible to "
"use in Node.js if you launch it as  ``node --experimental-wasm-stack-"
"switching``. (`#3400 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3400>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:146
msgid ""
"Added the ``proxy_is_tunneling`` property to ``HTTPConnection`` and "
"``HTTPSConnection``. (`#3285 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3285>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:147
msgid ""
"Added pickling support to ``NewConnectionError`` and "
"``NameResolutionError``. (`#3480 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3480>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:153
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue in debug logs where the HTTP version was rendering as "
"\"HTTP/11\" instead of \"HTTP/1.1\". (`#3489 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/3489>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:157 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:195
msgid "Deprecations and Removals"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:159
msgid ""
"Removed support for Python 3.8. (`#3492 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3492>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:163
msgid "2.2.3 (2024-09-12)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:168
msgid ""
"Added support for Python 3.13. (`#3473 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3473>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:173
msgid ""
"Fixed the default encoding of chunked request bodies to be UTF-8 instead of "
"ISO-8859-1. All other methods of supplying a request body already use UTF-8 "
"starting in urllib3 v2.0. (`#3053 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3053>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:175
msgid ""
"Fixed ResourceWarning on CONNECT with Python < 3.11.4 by backporting https://"
"github.com/python/cpython/issues/103472. (`#3252 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/3252>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:176
msgid ""
"Adjust tolerance for floating-point comparison on Windows to avoid flakiness "
"in CI (`#3413 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3413>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:177
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash where certain standard library hash functions were absent in "
"restricted environments. (`#3432 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3432>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:178
msgid ""
"Fixed mypy error when adding to ``HTTPConnection.default_socket_options``. "
"(`#3448 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3448>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:181
msgid "HTTP/2 (experimental)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:183
msgid "HTTP/2 support is still in early development."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:185
msgid ""
"Excluded Transfer-Encoding: chunked from HTTP/2 request body (`#3425 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3425>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:186
msgid "Added version checking for ``h2`` (https://pypi.org/project/h2/) usage."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:188
msgid ""
"Now only accepting supported h2 major version 4.x.x. (`#3290 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3290>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:189
msgid ""
"Added a probing mechanism for determining whether a given target origin "
"supports HTTP/2 via ALPN. (`#3301 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3301>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:191
msgid ""
"Add support for sending a request body with HTTP/2 (`#3302 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3302>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:197
msgid ""
"Note for downstream distributors: the ``_version.py`` file has been removed "
"and is now created at build time by hatch-vcs. (`#3412 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/3412>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:198
msgid ""
"Drop support for end-of-life PyPy3.8 and PyPy3.9. (`#3475 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3475>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:202
msgid "2.2.2 (2024-06-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:204 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:441
msgid ""
"Added the ``Proxy-Authorization`` header to the list of headers to strip "
"from requests when redirecting to a different host. As before, different "
"headers can be set via ``Retry.remove_headers_on_redirect``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:205
msgid ""
"Allowed passing negative integers as ``amt`` to read methods of ``http."
"client.HTTPResponse`` as an alternative to ``None``. (`#3122 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3122>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:206
msgid ""
"Fixed return types representing copying actions to use ``typing.Self``. "
"(`#3363 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3363>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:209
msgid "2.2.1 (2024-02-16)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:211
msgid ""
"Fixed issue where ``InsecureRequestWarning`` was emitted for HTTPS "
"connections when using Emscripten. (`#3331 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/3331>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:212
msgid ""
"Fixed ``HTTPConnectionPool.urlopen`` to stop automatically casting non-proxy "
"headers to ``HTTPHeaderDict``. This change was premature as it did not apply "
"to proxy headers and ``HTTPHeaderDict`` does not handle byte header values "
"correctly yet. (`#3343 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3343>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:213
msgid ""
"Changed ``InvalidChunkLength`` to ``ProtocolError`` when response terminates "
"before the chunk length is sent. (`#2860 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2860>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:214
msgid ""
"Changed ``ProtocolError`` to be more verbose on incomplete reads with excess "
"content. (`#3261 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3261>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:218
msgid "2.2.0 (2024-01-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:220
msgid ""
"Added support for `Emscripten and Pyodide <https://urllib3.readthedocs.io/en/"
"latest/reference/contrib/emscripten.html>`__, including streaming support in "
"cross-origin isolated browser environments where threading is enabled. "
"(`#2951 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2951>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:221
msgid ""
"Added support for ``HTTPResponse.read1()`` method. (`#3186 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3186>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:222
msgid ""
"Added rudimentary support for HTTP/2. (`#3284 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/3284>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:223
msgid ""
"Fixed issue where requests against urls with trailing dots were failing due "
"to SSL errors when using proxy. (`#2244 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2244>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:225
msgid ""
"Fixed ``HTTPConnection.proxy_is_verified`` and ``HTTPSConnection."
"proxy_is_verified`` to be always set to a boolean after connecting to a "
"proxy. It could be ``None`` in some cases previously. (`#3130 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3130>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:228
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue where ``headers`` passed in a request with ``json=`` would be "
"mutated (`#3203 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3203>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:229
msgid ""
"Fixed ``HTTPSConnection.is_verified`` to be set to ``False`` when connecting "
"from a HTTPS proxy to an HTTP target. It was set to ``True`` previously. "
"(`#3267 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3267>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:231
msgid ""
"Fixed handling of new error message from OpenSSL 3.2.0 when configuring an "
"HTTP proxy as HTTPS (`#3268 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3268>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:232
msgid ""
"Fixed TLS 1.3 post-handshake auth when the server certificate validation is "
"disabled (`#3325 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3325>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:233
msgid ""
"Note for downstream distributors: To run integration tests, you now need to "
"run the tests a second time with the ``--integration`` pytest flag. (`#3181 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3181>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:238
msgid "2.1.0 (2023-11-13)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:240
msgid ""
"Removed support for the deprecated urllib3[secure] extra. (`#2680 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2680>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:241
msgid ""
"Removed support for the deprecated SecureTransport TLS implementation. "
"(`#2681 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2681>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:242
msgid ""
"Removed support for the end-of-life Python 3.7. (`#3143 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/3143>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:243
msgid ""
"Allowed loading CA certificates from memory for proxies. (`#3065 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3065>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:244
msgid ""
"Fixed decoding Gzip-encoded responses which specified ``x-gzip`` content-"
"encoding. (`#3174 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3174>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:248
msgid "2.0.7 (2023-10-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:250 ../../../../CHANGES.rst:447
msgid ""
"Made body stripped from HTTP requests changing the request method to GET "
"after HTTP 303 \"See Other\" redirect responses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:254
msgid "2.0.6 (2023-10-02)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:256
msgid ""
"Added the ``Cookie`` header to the list of headers to strip from requests "
"when redirecting to a different host. As before, different headers can be "
"set via ``Retry.remove_headers_on_redirect``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:260
msgid "2.0.5 (2023-09-20)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:262
msgid ""
"Allowed pyOpenSSL third-party module without any deprecation warning. "
"(`#3126 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3126>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:263
msgid ""
"Fixed default ``blocksize`` of ``HTTPConnection`` classes to match high-"
"level classes. Previously was 8KiB, now 16KiB. (`#3066 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/3066>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:267
msgid "2.0.4 (2023-07-19)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:269
msgid ""
"Added support for union operators to ``HTTPHeaderDict`` (`#2254 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2254>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:270
msgid ""
"Added ``BaseHTTPResponse`` to ``urllib3.__all__`` (`#3078 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3078>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:271
msgid ""
"Fixed ``urllib3.connection.HTTPConnection`` to raise the ``http.client."
"connect`` audit event to have the same behavior as the standard library HTTP "
"client (`#2757 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2757>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:272
msgid ""
"Relied on the standard library for checking hostnames in supported PyPy "
"releases (`#3087 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3087>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:276
msgid "2.0.3 (2023-06-07)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:278
msgid ""
"Allowed alternative SSL libraries such as LibreSSL, while still issuing a "
"warning as we cannot help users facing issues with implementations other "
"than OpenSSL. (`#3020 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3020>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:279
msgid ""
"Deprecated URLs which don't have an explicit scheme (`#2950 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/pull/2950>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:280
msgid ""
"Fixed response decoding with Zstandard when compressed data is made of "
"several frames. (`#3008 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3008>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:281
msgid ""
"Fixed ``assert_hostname=False`` to correctly skip hostname check. (`#3051 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3051>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:285
msgid "2.0.2 (2023-05-03)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:287
msgid ""
"Fixed ``HTTPResponse.stream()`` to continue yielding bytes if buffered "
"decompressed data was still available to be read even if the underlying "
"socket is closed. This prevents a compressed response from being truncated. "
"(`#3009 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3009>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:293
msgid "2.0.1 (2023-04-30)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:295
msgid ""
"Fixed a socket leak when fingerprint or hostname verifications fail. (`#2991 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2991>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:296
msgid ""
"Fixed an error when ``HTTPResponse.read(0)`` was the first ``read`` call or "
"when the internal response body buffer was otherwise empty. (`#2998 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2998>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:300
msgid "2.0.0 (2023-04-26)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:302
msgid ""
"Read the `v2.0 migration guide <https://urllib3.readthedocs.io/en/latest/v2-"
"migration-guide.html>`__ for help upgrading to the latest version of urllib3."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:305
msgid "Removed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:307
msgid ""
"Removed support for Python 2.7, 3.5, and 3.6 (`#883 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/883>`__, `#2336 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2336>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:308
msgid ""
"Removed fallback on certificate ``commonName`` in ``match_hostname()`` "
"function. This behavior was deprecated in May 2000 in RFC 2818. Instead only "
"``subjectAltName`` is used to verify the hostname by default. To enable "
"verifying the hostname against ``commonName`` use ``SSLContext."
"hostname_checks_common_name = True`` (`#2113 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2113>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:312
msgid ""
"Removed support for Python with an ``ssl`` module compiled with LibreSSL, "
"CiscoSSL, wolfSSL, and all other OpenSSL alternatives. Python is moving to "
"require OpenSSL with PEP 644 (`#2168 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2168>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:314
msgid ""
"Removed support for OpenSSL versions earlier than 1.1.1 or that don't have "
"SNI support. When an incompatible OpenSSL version is detected an "
"``ImportError`` is raised (`#2168 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2168>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:316
msgid ""
"Removed the list of default ciphers for OpenSSL 1.1.1+ and SecureTransport "
"as their own defaults are already secure (`#2082 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2082>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:317
msgid ""
"Removed ``urllib3.contrib.appengine.AppEngineManager`` and support for "
"Google App Engine Standard Environment (`#2044 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2044>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:318
msgid ""
"Removed deprecated ``Retry`` options ``method_whitelist``, "
"``DEFAULT_REDIRECT_HEADERS_BLACKLIST`` (`#2086 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2086>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:319
msgid ""
"Removed ``urllib3.HTTPResponse.from_httplib`` (`#2648 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/2648>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:320
msgid ""
"Removed default value of ``None`` for the ``request_context`` parameter of "
"``urllib3.PoolManager.connection_from_pool_key``. This change should have no "
"effect on users as the default value of ``None`` was an invalid option and "
"was never used (`#1897 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1897>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:321
msgid ""
"Removed the ``urllib3.request`` module. ``urllib3.request.RequestMethods`` "
"has been made a private API. This change was made to ensure that ``from "
"urllib3 import request`` imported the top-level ``request()`` function "
"instead of the ``urllib3.request`` module (`#2269 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/2269>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:324
msgid ""
"Removed support for SSLv3.0 from the ``urllib3.contrib.pyopenssl`` even when "
"support is available from the compiled OpenSSL library (`#2233 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2233>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:325
msgid ""
"Removed the deprecated ``urllib3.contrib.ntlmpool`` module (`#2339 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2339>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:326
msgid ""
"Removed ``DEFAULT_CIPHERS``, ``HAS_SNI``, "
"``USE_DEFAULT_SSLCONTEXT_CIPHERS``, from the private module ``urllib3.util."
"ssl_`` (`#2168 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2168>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:327
msgid ""
"Removed ``urllib3.exceptions.SNIMissingWarning`` (`#2168 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/2168>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:328
msgid ""
"Removed the ``_prepare_conn`` method from ``HTTPConnectionPool``. Previously "
"this was only used to call ``HTTPSConnection.set_cert()`` by "
"``HTTPSConnectionPool`` (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:329
msgid ""
"Removed ``tls_in_tls_required`` property from ``HTTPSConnection``. This is "
"now determined from the ``scheme`` parameter in ``HTTPConnection."
"set_tunnel()`` (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:330
msgid ""
"Removed the ``strict`` parameter/attribute from ``HTTPConnection``, "
"``HTTPSConnection``, ``HTTPConnectionPool``, ``HTTPSConnectionPool``, and "
"``HTTPResponse`` (`#2064 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2064>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:333
msgid "Deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:335
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``HTTPResponse.getheaders()`` and ``HTTPResponse.getheader()`` "
"which will be removed in urllib3 v2.1.0. Instead use ``HTTPResponse."
"headers`` and ``HTTPResponse.headers.get(name, default)``. (`#1543 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1543>`__, `#2814 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/2814>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:336
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``urllib3.contrib.pyopenssl`` module which will be removed in "
"urllib3 v2.1.0 (`#2691 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2691>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:337
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``urllib3.contrib.securetransport`` module which will be removed "
"in urllib3 v2.1.0 (`#2692 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2692>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:338
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``ssl_version`` option in favor of ``ssl_minimum_version``. "
"``ssl_version`` will be removed in urllib3 v2.1.0 (`#2110 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2110>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:339
msgid ""
"Deprecated the ``strict`` parameter of ``PoolManager."
"connection_from_context()`` as it's not longer needed in Python 3.x. It will "
"be removed in urllib3 v2.1.0 (`#2267 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2267>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:340
msgid ""
"Deprecated the ``NewConnectionError.pool`` attribute which will be removed "
"in urllib3 v2.1.0 (`#2271 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2271>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:341
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``format_header_param_html5`` and ``format_header_param`` in "
"favor of ``format_multipart_header_param`` (`#2257 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/2257>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:342
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``RequestField.header_formatter`` parameter which will be removed "
"in urllib3 v2.1.0 (`#2257 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2257>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:343
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``HTTPSConnection.set_cert()`` method. Instead pass parameters to "
"the ``HTTPSConnection`` constructor (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:344
msgid ""
"Deprecated ``HTTPConnection.request_chunked()`` method which will be removed "
"in urllib3 v2.1.0. Instead pass ``chunked=True`` to ``HTTPConnection."
"request()`` (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:347
msgid "Added"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:349
msgid ""
"Added top-level ``urllib3.request`` function which uses a preconfigured "
"module-global ``PoolManager`` instance (`#2150 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2150>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:350
msgid ""
"Added the ``json`` parameter to ``urllib3.request()``, ``PoolManager."
"request()``, and ``ConnectionPool.request()`` methods to send JSON bodies in "
"requests. Using this parameter will set the header ``Content-Type: "
"application/json`` if ``Content-Type`` isn't already defined. Added support "
"for parsing JSON response bodies with ``HTTPResponse.json()`` method (`#2243 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2243>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:352
msgid ""
"Added type hints to the ``urllib3`` module (`#1897 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/1897>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:353
msgid ""
"Added ``ssl_minimum_version`` and ``ssl_maximum_version`` options which set "
"``SSLContext.minimum_version`` and ``SSLContext.maximum_version`` (`#2110 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2110>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:355
msgid ""
"Added support for Zstandard (RFC 8878) when ``zstandard`` 1.18.0 or later is "
"installed. Added the ``zstd`` extra which installs the ``zstandard`` package "
"(`#1992 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1992>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:357
msgid ""
"Added ``urllib3.response.BaseHTTPResponse`` class. All future response "
"classes will be subclasses of ``BaseHTTPResponse`` (`#2083 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2083>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:358
msgid ""
"Added ``FullPoolError`` which is raised when ``PoolManager(block=True)`` and "
"a connection is returned to a full pool (`#2197 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2197>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:359
msgid ""
"Added ``HTTPHeaderDict`` to the top-level ``urllib3`` namespace (`#2216 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2216>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:360
msgid ""
"Added support for configuring header merging behavior with HTTPHeaderDict "
"When using a ``HTTPHeaderDict`` to provide headers for a request, by default "
"duplicate header values will be repeated. But if ``combine=True`` is passed "
"into a call to ``HTTPHeaderDict.add``, then the added header value will be "
"merged in with an existing value into a comma-separated list (``X-My-Header: "
"foo, bar``) (`#2242 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2242>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:365
msgid ""
"Added ``NameResolutionError`` exception when a DNS error occurs (`#2305 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2305>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:366
msgid ""
"Added ``proxy_assert_hostname`` and ``proxy_assert_fingerprint`` kwargs to "
"``ProxyManager`` (`#2409 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2409>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:367
msgid ""
"Added a configurable ``backoff_max`` parameter to the ``Retry`` class. If a "
"custom ``backoff_max`` is provided to the ``Retry`` class, it will replace "
"the ``Retry.DEFAULT_BACKOFF_MAX`` (`#2494 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2494>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:370
msgid ""
"Added the ``authority`` property to the Url class as per RFC 3986 3.2. This "
"property should be used in place of ``netloc`` for users who want to include "
"the userinfo (auth) component of the URI (`#2520 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2520>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:371
msgid ""
"Added the ``scheme`` parameter to ``HTTPConnection.set_tunnel`` to configure "
"the scheme of the origin being tunnelled to (`#1985 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:372
msgid ""
"Added the ``is_closed``, ``is_connected`` and ``has_connected_to_proxy`` "
"properties to ``HTTPConnection`` (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:373
msgid ""
"Added optional ``backoff_jitter`` parameter to ``Retry``. (`#2952 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2952>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:376
msgid "Changed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:378
msgid ""
"Changed ``urllib3.response.HTTPResponse.read`` to respect the semantics of "
"``io.BufferedIOBase`` regardless of compression. Specifically, this method:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:380
msgid ""
"Only returns an empty bytes object to indicate EOF (that is, the response "
"has been fully consumed)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:381
msgid "Never returns more bytes than requested."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:382
msgid "Can issue any number of system calls: zero, one or multiple."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:384
msgid ""
"If you want each ``urllib3.response.HTTPResponse.read`` call to issue a "
"single system call, you need to disable decompression by setting "
"``decode_content=False`` (`#2128 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2128>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:385
msgid ""
"Changed ``urllib3.HTTPConnection.getresponse`` to return an instance of "
"``urllib3.HTTPResponse`` instead of ``http.client.HTTPResponse`` (`#2648 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2648>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:386
msgid ""
"Changed ``ssl_version`` to instead set the corresponding ``SSLContext."
"minimum_version`` and ``SSLContext.maximum_version`` values.  Regardless of "
"``ssl_version`` passed ``SSLContext`` objects are now constructed using "
"``ssl.PROTOCOL_TLS_CLIENT`` (`#2110 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2110>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:389
msgid ""
"Changed default ``SSLContext.minimum_version`` to be ``TLSVersion.TLSv1_2`` "
"in line with Python 3.10 (`#2373 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2373>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:390
msgid ""
"Changed ``ProxyError`` to wrap any connection error (timeout, TLS, DNS) that "
"occurs when connecting to the proxy (`#2482 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/pull/2482>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:391
msgid ""
"Changed ``urllib3.util.create_urllib3_context`` to not override the system "
"cipher suites with a default value. The new default will be cipher suites "
"configured by the operating system (`#2168 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2168>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:393
msgid ""
"Changed ``multipart/form-data`` header parameter formatting matches the "
"WHATWG HTML Standard as of 2021-06-10. Control characters in filenames are "
"no longer percent encoded (`#2257 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2257>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:394
msgid ""
"Changed the error raised when connecting via HTTPS when the ``ssl`` module "
"isn't available from ``SSLError`` to ``ImportError`` (`#2589 <https://github."
"com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2589>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:395
msgid ""
"Changed ``HTTPConnection.request()`` to always use lowercase chunk "
"boundaries when sending requests with ``Transfer-Encoding: chunked`` (`#2515 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2515>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:396
msgid ""
"Changed ``enforce_content_length`` default to True, preventing silent data "
"loss when reading streamed responses (`#2514 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2514>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:397
msgid ""
"Changed internal implementation of ``HTTPHeaderDict`` to use ``dict`` "
"instead of ``collections.OrderedDict`` for better performance (`#2080 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2080>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:398
msgid ""
"Changed the ``urllib3.contrib.pyopenssl`` module to wrap ``OpenSSL.SSL."
"Error`` with ``ssl.SSLError`` in ``PyOpenSSLContext.load_cert_chain`` "
"(`#2628 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2628>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:399
msgid ""
"Changed usage of the deprecated ``socket.error`` to ``OSError`` (`#2120 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2120>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:400
msgid ""
"Changed all parameters in the ``HTTPConnection`` and ``HTTPSConnection`` "
"constructors to be keyword-only except ``host`` and ``port`` (`#1985 "
"<https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:401
msgid ""
"Changed ``HTTPConnection.getresponse()`` to set the socket timeout from "
"``HTTPConnection.timeout`` value before reading data from the socket. This "
"previously was done manually by the ``HTTPConnectionPool`` calling "
"``HTTPConnection.sock.settimeout(...)`` (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:403
msgid ""
"Changed the ``_proxy_host`` property to ``_tunnel_host`` in "
"``HTTPConnectionPool`` to more closely match how the property is used (value "
"in ``HTTPConnection.set_tunnel()``) (`#1985 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/1985>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:404
msgid ""
"Changed name of ``Retry.BACK0FF_MAX`` to be ``Retry.DEFAULT_BACKOFF_MAX``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:405
msgid ""
"Changed TLS handshakes to use ``SSLContext.check_hostname`` when possible "
"(`#2452 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/pull/2452>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:406
msgid ""
"Changed ``server_hostname`` to behave like other parameters only used by "
"``HTTPSConnectionPool`` (`#2537 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"pull/2537>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:407
msgid ""
"Changed the default ``blocksize`` to 16KB to match OpenSSL's default read "
"amounts (`#2348 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/pull/2348>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:408
msgid ""
"Changed ``HTTPResponse.read()`` to raise an error when calling with "
"``decode_content=False`` after using ``decode_content=True`` to prevent data "
"loss (`#2800 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2800>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:411
msgid "Fixed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:413
msgid ""
"Fixed thread-safety issue where accessing a ``PoolManager`` with many "
"distinct origins would cause connection pools to be closed while requests "
"are in progress (`#1252 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/1252>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:414
msgid ""
"Fixed an issue where an ``HTTPConnection`` instance would erroneously reuse "
"the socket read timeout value from reading the previous response instead of "
"a newly configured connect timeout. Instead now if ``HTTPConnection."
"timeout`` is updated before sending the next request the new timeout value "
"will be used (`#2645 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2645>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:416
msgid ""
"Fixed ``socket.error.errno`` when raised from pyOpenSSL's ``OpenSSL.SSL."
"SysCallError`` (`#2118 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/2118>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:417
msgid ""
"Fixed the default value of ``HTTPSConnection.socket_options`` to match "
"``HTTPConnection`` (`#2213 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2213>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:418
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug where ``headers`` would be modified by the "
"``remove_headers_on_redirect`` feature (`#2272 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/issues/2272>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:419
msgid ""
"Fixed a reference cycle bug in ``urllib3.util.connection."
"create_connection()`` (`#2277 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/2277>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:420
msgid ""
"Fixed a socket leak if ``HTTPConnection.connect()`` fails (`#2571 <https://"
"github.com/urllib3/urllib3/pull/2571>`__)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:421
msgid ""
"Fixed ``urllib3.contrib.pyopenssl.WrappedSocket`` and ``urllib3.contrib."
"securetransport.WrappedSocket`` close methods (`#2970 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/issues/2970>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:424
msgid "1.26.20 (2024-08-29)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:426
msgid ""
"Fixed a crash where certain standard library hash functions were absent in "
"FIPS-compliant environments. (`#3432 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"issues/3432>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:429
msgid ""
"Replaced deprecated dash-separated setuptools entries in ``setup.cfg``. "
"(`#3461 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/pull/3461>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:431
msgid ""
"Took into account macOS setting ``ECONNRESET`` instead of ``EPROTOTYPE`` in "
"its newer versions. (`#3416 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/"
"pull/3416>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:434
msgid ""
"Backported changes to our tests and CI configuration from v2.x to support "
"testing with CPython 3.12 and 3.13. (`#3436 <https://github.com/urllib3/"
"urllib3/pull/3436>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:439
msgid "1.26.19 (2024-06-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:442
msgid ""
"Fixed handling of OpenSSL 3.2.0 new error message for misconfiguring an HTTP "
"proxy as HTTPS. (`#3405 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/issues/3405>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:445
msgid "1.26.18 (2023-10-17)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:450
msgid "1.26.17 (2023-10-02)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:452
msgid ""
"Added the ``Cookie`` header to the list of headers to strip from requests "
"when redirecting to a different host. As before, different headers can be "
"set via ``Retry.remove_headers_on_redirect``. (`#3139 <https://github.com/"
"urllib3/urllib3/pull/3139>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:455
msgid "1.26.16 (2023-05-23)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:457
msgid ""
"Fixed thread-safety issue where accessing a ``PoolManager`` with many "
"distinct origins would cause connection pools to be closed while requests "
"are in progress (`#2954 <https://github.com/urllib3/urllib3/pull/2954>`_)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../CHANGES.rst:461
msgid "1.26.15 (2023-03-10)"
msgstr ""

